  <!-- ⑦ USE CASES (BENTO) -->
  <section class="use-cases-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header reveal-el">
        <div class="section-badge">Use Cases</div>
        <h2 class="section-title">Designed for <span>modern workflows.</span></h2>
        <p class="section-desc">From legacy refactoring to onboarding developers, Anuvaad scales to fit every level of engineering development.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bento-grid">
        <div class="bento-card bento-card-large reveal-el">
          <div class="bento-card-bg-code">
            // Onboarding code<br>
            import { setupUser } from './auth';<br>
            const user = setupUser();<br>
            log('User connected', user.id);
          </div>
          <h3>Developer Onboarding</h3>
          <p>Accelerate onboarding. Give new team members a companion that explains complex, undocumented codebases line-by-line.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bento-card reveal-el">
          <div class="bento-card-bg-code">
            def parse_data(d):<br>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;return [x for x in d if x.valid]
          </div>
          <h3>Code Reviews</h3>
          <p>Translate pull request diffs into clean explanations, allowing non-technical stakeholders to audit logic flows.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bento-card reveal-el">
          <div class="bento-card-bg-code">
            // C++ pointers<br>
            int* ptr = &val;<br>
            std::cout &lt;&lt; *ptr;
          </div>
          <h3>Legacy Refactoring</h3>
          <p>Translate old systems in C++, Java, or Fortran to Kotlin, Rust, or Go with proper idiomatic translations.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bento-card bento-card-large reveal-el">
          <div class="bento-card-bg-code">
            package main<br>
            import "fmt"<br>
            func main() { fmt.Println("Go migration complete!") }
          </div>
          <h3>Language Migration</h3>
          <p>Migrate whole services between programming languages. Automatically rewrite core logic while mapping idiomatic functions.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bento-card reveal-el">
          <div class="bento-card-bg-code">
            /** SQL queries */<br>
            SELECT users.name, billing.amount<br>
            FROM users JOIN billing ON users.id = billing.uid;
          </div>
          <h3>SQL & Query Parsing</h3>
          <p>Translate nested, complex SQL statements or GraphQL schemas to English logic breakdowns, instantly.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bento-card bento-card-large reveal-el">
          <div class="bento-card-bg-code">
            # API Documentation<br>
            ## POST /api/translate<br>
            Parameters: code, source, target...
          </div>
          <h3>Technical Documentation</h3>
          <p>Auto-generate clean explanations and formatting for your system logic. Export to Markdown and drop directly into README files or wikis.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

